<TITLE> Stop price rise on new pay scale: PM </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 25 (bdnews24.com)Prime minister Sheikh Hasina has asked the cabinet to see to it that prices of essentials do not go up on implementation of the National Pay Commission recommendations. Hasina told her cabinet colleagues at a meeting on Monday that the commission proposals should be implemented in a way so that the essential goods remain within the reach of people's purchase capacity, her press secretary Abul Kalam Azad told reporters after the meeting. According to the recommendations submitted on Apr 23, the highest and lowest pay scale are Tk 45,000 and Tk 4,000 respectively and government officials will have to pay income tax. Transport facilities will be given in five to seven years, suggested the commission formed on Aug 31 last year. Azad said a seven-member committee was formed to review the salary structure. The committee will submit a report in one and a half months. Secretaries to the cabinet, finance, defence, prime minister's office, establishment, law and planning are in the committee. The cabinet meeting also provisionally approved the Jamuna Multipurpose Bridge Authority (Amendment) Act 2009 and give final endorsement to Real Estate Development and Management Act (Amendment), 2009. The meeting also discussed cyclonic storm "Aila" and possible post-disaster management. bdn
